claim.claim-text:
1. A method of fabricating a liquid crystal display device, comprising:
forming a plurality of thin film transistors, gate pads and data pads on a first substrate;
forming a passivation layer on the first substrate and over the plurality of thin film transistors;
forming a plurality of organic pixel electrodes along with a plurality of organic conductive electrodes on the passivation layer, wherein the plurality of organic pixel electrodes electrically connect to the plurality of thin film transistors and wherein each of the plurality of organic conductive electrodes electrically connects to the gate pads and data pads;
attaching the first substrate to a second substrate such that a gap exists between the first substrate and the second substrate; and
interposing a liquid crystal in the gap,
wherein forming a plurality of organic pixel electrodes includes:
forming an organic polymer layer on the first substrate; and
selectively exposing portions of the organic polymer layer to light so as to make the exposed portions electrically-conductive and to make the unexposed portions non-conductive.

2. The method of claim 1, wherein forming the plurality of thin film transistors includes:
forming a gate electrode on the first substrate;
forming a gate insulating layer over the first substrate and over the gate electrode;
forming a semiconductor layer on the gate insulating layer and over the gate electrode; and
forming a source electrode and a drain electrode on the semiconductor layer.

11. A method of fabricating a liquid crystal display device, comprising:
forming a gate line and a crossing data line on a substrate;
forming a gate pad and a data pad on the substrate;
forming a thin film transistor on the substrate and adjacent to the crossing;
forming a passivation layer over the substrate, including over the thin film transistor; and
forming an organic pixel electrode along with organic conductive electrodes on the passivation layer, the organic conductive electrodes electrically connecting to the gate and data pads,
wherein forming an organic pixel electrode includes:
forming an organic polymer layer on the passivation layer; and
illuminating selected portions of the organic polymer layer so as to render the illuminated portions electrically-conductive and to make un-illuminated portions non-conductive.
